---
alwaysApply: false
---
Add a new feature or enhancement to the project. Make sure your implementation is well-tested and integrates cleanly with the existing codebase.

- Before starting, create a new branch for your feature:
- Implement your feature/enhancement. Make sure to:
  - Follow the existing code style and structure.
  - Add or update tests in the `tests/` directory to cover your changes.
  - Run all tests:
  - If your feature affects output (e.g., summary markdown), manually inspect the output files in `output/` to ensure correctness.
- If you add new breaking functionality, add end-to-end tests and check the actual output, not just test assertions.
- Once everything passes, push your branch and open a pull request
- In your PR description, clearly explain:
  - What the feature/enhancement is
  - How it was tested (if the testing method changed)
  - Any new dependencies or config changes